snippet.textDisplay:
There's a certain osmosis that music has with its environment, every song or piece has an atmosphere of its own. Strings or anybody doesn't have the right to fuck with it.

The conclusive, redundant flute solo, is nothing but irresistible intellectual masturbation, the ability of not being able to control yourself from showing off. Completely spoils the beautiful rendition built up for so long by the Niazi Brothers, and more importantly, takes away from the spirit of the song.
